{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χίμαιρ-α</b> [ῐ], ἡ, <br /> <b>she-goat,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.181, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 322, “PCair.Zen.” 576.3 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; sacrificed before battle to Ἄρτεμις Ἀγροτέρα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 232 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 3.2.12, “HG” 4.2.20, “Lac.” 13.8; θαλλὸν χιμαίραις προσφέρων 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 502 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>a young she-goat</b> (compare χίμαρος), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 523a1; χ. ἐξ αἰγῶν \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<b>kid,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Lev.4.28, 29. \">LXX</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> Χίμαιρα, ἡ, <b>Chimaera,</b> a fire-breathing monster, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.179, compare 16.328; 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 319, etc.; χ. πύρπνοος 4th c.BC: Anaxilas Comicus 22.3 (troch.), Epinic. 2.10. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> explained as mythical for a volcano in Lycia, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 14.3.5. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9732","accentedUnicode":"χίμαιρα","shortDef":"a yearling","mediumDef":"a yearling","stepGloss":"a yearling","stepTransliteration":"chimaira","_step_Type":"word"}]}